David and Goliath
<COREF ID="54" TYPE="IDENT">Grace Kuo</COREF> comments that nylon 66 was a new fiber with good elasticity , high strength and a soft , bulky feel , along with good resistance to ultraviolet light .
Adding just 15 to 20 % of nylon 66 to <COREF ID="4" TYPE="IDENT">a fabric</COREF> <COREF ID="24" TYPE="IDENT">transforms</COREF> <COREF ID="4" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> , making <COREF ID="4" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> thoroughly suited to modern - day demands for " healthy , comfortable " clothing .
<COREF ID="71" TYPE="IDENT">The big international manufacturers</COREF> had realized <COREF ID="24" TYPE="IDENT">this</COREF> and adopted an oligarchic strategy : as well as making it difficult for others to obtain the raw materials , <COREF ID="71" TYPE="IDENT">they</COREF> were very careful not to reveal any of <COREF ID="71" TYPE="IDENT">their</COREF> manufacturing know - how .
